## Issue: `items` is not defined in the Code node

In n8n's Code node, the input items are **not** available as a variable called `items`. You need to use `$input.all()` to access them.

### The Problem

```javascript
// ❌ This will throw a ReferenceError: items is not defined
const items = items.map(i => ({ json: { doubled: i.json.n * 2 } }));
return items;
```

### The Fix

```javascript
// ✅ Use $input.all() to get the incoming items
const items = $input.all();
return items.map(i => ({ json: { doubled: i.json.n * 2 } }));
```

### Why This Works

- `$input.all()` returns the array of items from the previous node
- Each item follows n8n's required [data structure](https://docs.n8n.io/data/data-structure/): an object with a `json` key containing your data
- The mapped output correctly wraps results in `{ json: { ... } }` as required by the [Code node](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/core-nodes/n8n-nodes-base.code/)

### Also Make Sure Your Trigger Sends `n`

Since you're reading `i.json.n`, your Manual Trigger needs data with an `n` field. You can add a **Set node** between the Manual Trigger and Code node to define `n`, or use the [Debug Helper node](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/core-nodes/n8n-nodes-base.debughelper/) to generate test data.
